@startuml runtime-e2e-6-1
title Scenario 6.1 - Parcours E2E CanTelcoX (cas nominal)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #A80036
  LifeLineBorderColor #CBD5E1
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  ParticipantBorderColor #1E3A5F
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #DBEAFE
  ActorBorderColor #2F3A4A
  ActorBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
}

actor Client
participant "API Gateway\nFastAPI" as Gateway
participant "identity-service" as Identity
participant "catalog-service" as Catalog
participant "order-service" as Orders
participant "line-service" as Lines
participant "billing-service" as Billing
participant "audit-service" as Audit
participant "free5GC core\nAMF/SMF/UDM/UDR/UPF" as Free5GC

Client -> Gateway : POST /v1/users\nprofil + consentements
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Identity : POST /v1/users
activate Identity
Identity -> Audit : trace creation profil
activate Audit
Audit --> Identity : 202 accepted
deactivate Audit
Identity --> Gateway : 201 profil cree
deactivate Identity
Gateway --> Client : 201 Created
deactivate Gateway

Client -> Gateway : POST /v1/auth/mfa/challenge
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Identity : POST /v1/auth/mfa/challenge
activate Identity
Identity --> Gateway : 201 challenge cree
deactivate Identity
Gateway --> Client : 201 challenge cree
deactivate Gateway

Client -> Gateway : POST /v1/auth/mfa/verify\ncode OTP
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Identity : POST /v1/auth/mfa/verify
activate Identity
Identity -> Audit : trace MFA valide
activate Audit
Audit --> Identity : 202 accepted
deactivate Audit
Identity --> Gateway : 200 token/session
deactivate Identity
Gateway --> Client : 200 token/session
deactivate Gateway

Client -> Gateway : GET /v1/catalog/plans
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Catalog : GET /v1/catalog/plans
activate Catalog
Catalog --> Gateway : 200 offres actives
deactivate Catalog
Gateway --> Client : 200 offres actives
deactivate Gateway

Client -> Gateway : POST /v1/orders\nIdempotency-Key: K
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Orders : POST /v1/orders\nIdempotency-Key: K
activate Orders
Orders -> Catalog : verifier offre + prix versionnes
activate Catalog
Catalog --> Orders : offre admissible
deactivate Catalog
Orders -> Identity : valider client / token
activate Identity
Identity --> Orders : client valide
deactivate Identity
Orders -> Billing : declarer commande facturable
activate Billing
Billing --> Orders : 202 accepted
deactivate Billing
Orders -> Lines : POST /v1/lines/activations\norderId, customerId, offer
activate Lines
Lines -> Free5GC : provisionner abonne / SIM\nSUPI, DNN, slice
activate Free5GC
Free5GC --> Lines : activation acceptee\netat reseau
deactivate Free5GC
Lines -> Audit : trace activation ligne
activate Audit
Audit --> Lines : 202 accepted
deactivate Audit
Lines --> Orders : 201 ligne active
deactivate Lines
Orders -> Audit : trace commande confirmee
activate Audit
Audit --> Orders : 202 accepted
deactivate Audit
Orders --> Gateway : 201 commande confirmee
deactivate Orders
Gateway --> Client : 201 commande confirmee
deactivate Gateway

Client -> Gateway : GET /v1/billing/usage
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Billing : GET /v1/billing/usage
activate Billing
Billing --> Gateway : 200 usage + facture
deactivate Billing
Gateway --> Client : 200 usage + facture
deactivate Gateway

note over Gateway,Free5GC
Le gateway conserve methode, chemin, corps, query params
et headers applicatifs comme Idempotency-Key.
L'integration free5GC reste encapsulee dans line-service;
order-service orchestre la commande sans provisionner le reseau.
end note
@enduml
